                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12615496" author="larsko" created="Tue, 22 Jul 2008 03:50:29 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch changing the maximum POST size to 1000000 bytes. Tested with the bundled Jetty version 6.1.3.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12615506" author="yseeley@gmail.com" created="Tue, 22 Jul 2008 05:20:00 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Are there any downsides to this configuration that anyone is aware of?&lt;br/&gt;
Does it in any way affect the resources needed to handle a small POST?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12615511" author="larsko" created="Tue, 22 Jul 2008 05:31:46 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve had a quick look at the source code; the only place where this parameter is used is when checking the size of the uploaded content and throwing an IllegalStateException when it&apos;s too large. It shouldn&apos;t affect the required resources at all.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12615513" author="yseeley@gmail.com" created="Tue, 22 Jul 2008 05:46:01 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Great, thanks for looking into that.  Committed.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
